"{\"content\":{\"body\":\"![](https://miro.medium.com/max/1400/1\\\\*a2n\\\\_9SEjzOYFNJ4e-zGaYQ.png)\\n\\n[![Parth panchal](https://miro.medium.com/fit/c/56/56/2\\\\*KI1G4U\\\\_2awb2j_tdkOW6JQ.jpeg)](https://parthpanchal53.medium.com/?source=post_page-----981811e2a73d-----------------------------------)\\n\\nToday , lets build a quick flutter **CRUD app** for storing movies using Firebase‚Äôs **Cloud **[**Firestore**](https://firebase.google.com/docs/firestore/)** database** and a simple** Riverpod Provider **.\\n\\n## Demo of what we are going to build :\\n\\n![](https://miro.medium.com/max/800/1\\\\*kWDuMVHKs6VaXmEsPvYZtw.gif)\\n\\n## Step 1 : Create a new flutter project.\\n\\nOpen up a new directory and within the terminal hit :\\n\\n    flutter create your_project_name \\n\\n![](https://miro.medium.com/max/1400/1\\\\*HLXGj0yet5J-CbBb6BxmVA.png)\\n\\nCreate Flutter Project\\n\\n## Step 2 : Setup a new Firebase Project .\\n\\nHere is a quick YouTube tutorial for your reference : [Fireship Flutter Firebase Setup](https://youtu.be/Mx24wiPilHg) (both Android/IOS setup). In the Firebase Console you will find Cloud Firestore option , hit create database in test mode and go with the default options . This will setup the firestore database for our flutter app .\\n\\n![](https://miro.medium.com/max/1400/1\\\\*dWxDN9-eo5KLqi4St-sLzg.png)\\n\\nCloud Firestore set-up\\n\\n## Step 3 : Add Firebase dependencies to Pubspec.yaml file.\\n\\nFor latest versions , head over to : [Dart packages](https://pub.dev/) and copy the latest versions . If you are using VS-code , then there is a handy extension([Pubspec Assist](https://marketplace.visualstudio.com/items?itemName=jeroen-meijer.pubspec-assist)) that helps you install latest dependencies by simply typing names .\\n\\n![](https://miro.medium.com/max/906/1\\\\*sUavMZEQAEktJvoUC0fFHw.png)\\n\\nFirebase Dependencies(Pubspec.yaml)\\n\\n**firebase_core** is needed for Core firebase functionalities and everytime you interact with firebase.\\n\\n**cloud_firestore **is needed to interact with our remote firestore database and perform CRUD operations from our flutter app.\\n\\n**flutter_riverpod **is needed for managing the state within our app .\\n\\n## Step 4 : Initialize our flutter app with Firebase.\\n\\nRefractor the sample Counter app code in main.dart file with the code given below .\\n\\nMain.dart\\n\\n    WidgetsFlutterBinding.ensureInitialized();\\n\\nThe above line has to be added compulsorily so that our flutter app can communicate with Firebase (It calls native API channels ) . Detailed info available [here](https://stackoverflow.com/questions/63873338/what-does-widgetsflutterbinding-ensureinitialized-do) .\\n\\n    await Firebase.initializeApp() ;\\n\\nThis initializes a new FirebaseApp instance by name and options and returns the created app. This method should be called before any usage of FlutterFire plugins.\\n\\nFinally , wrap the MaterialApp with a ***ProviderScope*** (a widget that stores the state of all providers used in the app), so as to access state from various widgets and contexts .\\n\\n## Step 5 : Lets setup the Movie model .\\n\\nCreate a new Folder called as Models and a file Movie.dart within it .For the sake of demo , lets have 3 simple fields i.e. ***movieName*** , ***posterURl*** and the length of the movie . (These are the fields that would be stored in firestore database as well).\\n\\n## Step 6 : Lets setup the Database class.\\n\\nThis Database class will contain all the methods that we will require to implement CRUD operations and manipulate the data in Firestore .\\n\\nDatabase Class\\n\\nOn line* ***49**, We create a simple **Riverpod Provider** called databaseProvider through which we can access the **instance **of our Database class and thus call all the Database methods through it.\\n\\n## Step 7 : Lets move to the UI (the JAZZY stuff) .\\n\\nLets start from the HomeScreen which is a simple stateless widget and displays the list of documents (movies) from Firestore database .\\n\\n## 1. HomeScreen.dart .\\n\\n## 2. MovieList.dart (A widget to list all the movies used by our HomeScreen).\\n\\n## 3. AddMovie.dart (Widget used to Add/Update a Movie) .\\n\\nAnd that‚Äôs it üî• ! Wasn‚Äôt that simple ?\\n\\nDo üëè for the blog if you learnt something from the blog üòÑ. Also comment down if you have any doubts or suggestions regarding anything.\\n\\n## Source Code for this Application :\\n\\nI keep playing with flutter and you can find all of my work below.\\n\\nGoodbye üëã , meet you in another blog in a while.\\n\",\"timestamp\":1640494710,\"title\":\"Flutter-Firebase(Firestore) CRUD App using Riverpod.\"},\"digest\":\"gz9mBtyK4PZV_5Ot5LoKda8Wd4LzQtAEi0eeruRQPCc\",\"authorship\":{\"contributor\":\"0xad95aefE6570D5FBFAF96874b34b09bD415Df757\",\"signingKey\":\"{\\\"crv\\\":\\\"P-256\\\",\\\"ext\\\":true,\\\"key_ops\\\":[\\\"verify\\\"],\\\"kty\\\":\\\"EC\\\",\\\"x\\\":\\\"5oRrlQCPQDTE5QZB8B4rEvqfjCIX7KRJvp4Hp5Xv0rI\\\",\\\"y\\\":\\\"a9JHPvMUzvWczFJkJHBr1Bjti_56xmWctWFmasjsPrk\\\"}\",\"signature\":\"GP8V4L-RC6tbbF9JUHPPY2mLt45crsZ0zF22q_H0y1IZqG7LFfIh0of2GFqkLmXkjQEt98KdfrMNVNqTl4--4A\",\"signingKeySignature\":\"0xb9bf6633d180c71aa5227d740e210dac2637e64d192ea2289e1f058b3527e7792b7d224ef7a851a2faede4354af100d53f3a4998a79f18fbf282d08b7ef0d7661c\",\"signingKeyMessage\":\"I authorize publishing on mirror.xyz from this device using:\\n{\\\"crv\\\":\\\"P-256\\\",\\\"ext\\\":true,\\\"key_ops\\\":[\\\"verify\\\"],\\\"kty\\\":\\\"EC\\\",\\\"x\\\":\\\"5oRrlQCPQDTE5QZB8B4rEvqfjCIX7KRJvp4Hp5Xv0rI\\\",\\\"y\\\":\\\"a9JHPvMUzvWczFJkJHBr1Bjti_56xmWctWFmasjsPrk\\\"}\",\"algorithm\":{\"name\":\"ECDSA\",\"hash\":\"SHA-256\"}},\"nft\":{},\"version\":\"12-21-2020\",\"originalDigest\":\"gz9mBtyK4PZV_5Ot5LoKda8Wd4LzQtAEi0eeruRQPCc\"}"